-- Toyota says won't restart most Japan plants next week
-- 
-- Tue Apr 5, 2011 9:50pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/04/06/us-toyota-production-idUSTRE73509020110406

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Toyota Motor Corp ( 7203.T ) said on Wednesday it would not restart production at most of its idled Japanese factories next week, denying a Nikkei newspaper report. 

 "There will be no resumption of production at most of our domestic factories next week," a Toyota spokeswoman said. The company will announce its decisions as they are made, she said. (Reporting by  Chang-Ran Kim ; Editing by Edmund Klamann)